node.text:
It's been 6 months since Mega Man X stopped Sigma and his Maverick uprising.. But a familiar foe has returned for revenge! The new and improved.. Storm Eagle L! Watch the full video on Youtube, link in bio! #SomethingSeries #MegaManX #TerminalMontage⠀
Special thanks to @funymony for his amazing work on backgrounds! And @MyNewSoundtrack for his awesome Storm Eagle remix!!

node.text: I always compare my wife and I to an alien and a robot, so I redid our avatars to reflect that.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jeremey (Terminalmontage) in Dreamland. May be an image of text that says 'rish The Kirby surname is one of several names that have both English and Irish origins. Kirby is place-name given to many areas in England, deriving from 'kirk' meaning 'church' and 'byr' meaning 'settlement' It later was taken as a surname in the form of de Kirkebi. https://irelandroots.com kirby Irish Surname Kirby Irish Roots'.

node.text: Kirbo Lore: The name Kirby is derived from "kirk" meaning 'church'
